{{!--
  ============================================================================
  FORM 3 NOTICE - SERVICE AND VALIDITY CHECKLIST
  ============================================================================
  Canonical checklist for England Section 8 notice packs.
--}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>{{notice_name}} - Service and Validity Checklist</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 10mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .doc-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 1.5em;
      padding-bottom: 1em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
    }

    .doc-header h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.4em 0;
      font-size: 14pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .doc-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      color: white;
      font-size: 10pt;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .summary-box,
    .checklist-box,
    .callout {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .summary-box,
    .checklist-box {
      margin: 1.25em 0;
      border: 1px solid #d8d8d8;
      background: #fff;
    }

    .summary-box {
      padding: 1em;
      background: #fafafa;
    }

    .summary-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 190px 1fr;
      gap: 0.45em 1em;
    }

    .summary-grid dt {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #444;
    }

    .summary-grid dd {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .section-title {
      margin: 1.75em 0 0.75em 0;
      padding-bottom: 0.4em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
      font-size: 12pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .checklist-box .heading {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0.7em 0.9em;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      color: white;
      font-size: 11pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .checklist-box .content {
      padding: 1em;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.4em 0 0 1.2em;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0.4em 0;
    }

    .callout {
      margin: 1.25em 0;
      padding: 1em;
      border-left: 4px solid #1a1a1a;
      background: #f7f7f7;
    }

    .callout.warning {
      border-color: #b45309;
      background: #fff7ed;
    }

    .callout.critical {
      border-color: #b91c1c;
      background: #fef2f2;
    }

    .doc-footer {
      margin-top: 2em;
      padding-top: 1em;
      border-top: 1px solid #d8d8d8;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="doc-header">
    <h1>Service and Validity Checklist</h1>
    <span class="doc-badge">{{notice_name}}</span>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Use this checklist to verify that the {{notice_name}} is internally consistent across the notice and support documents, has been served using a defensible method, and is ready for evidence use if a claim is issued.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="summary-box">
    <dl class="summary-grid">
      <dt>Landlord</dt>
      <dd>{{landlord_full_name}}</dd>
      <dt>Tenant</dt>
      <dd>{{tenant_full_name}}{{#if tenant_2_name}}, {{tenant_2_name}}{{/if}}</dd>
      <dt>Property</dt>
      <dd>{{property_address}}</dd>
      {{#if (hasValue tenancy_start_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Tenancy start date</dt>
      <dd>{{tenancy_start_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue service_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice service date</dt>
      <dd>{{service_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue notice_expiry_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice expiry date</dt>
      <dd>{{notice_expiry_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue earliest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Earliest proceedings date</dt>
      <dd>{{earliest_proceedings_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if ground_descriptions}}
      <dt>Grounds relied on</dt>
      <dd>{{ground_descriptions}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Service Evidence</h2>
  <div class="checklist-box">
    <div class="heading">Keep With The Pack</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>A copy of the completed {{notice_name}} that was served.</li>
        <li>A note of the service date, time, place, and method.</li>
        <li>Proof of posting, tracking, witness details, or photographs, depending on the service method used.</li>
        <li>Any follow-up correspondence showing the tenant received or responded to the notice.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Validity Checks</h2>
  <div class="checklist-box">
    <div class="heading">Before You Rely On The Notice</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>The pack uses the same canonical notice timeline across the notice, proof of service, summary, and bundle documents.</li>
        <li>The correct prescribed notice form is used for the case.</li>
        <li>The landlord, tenant, and property details are complete and match the tenancy records.</li>
        <li>Each ground relied on is identified clearly and supported with particulars.</li>
        <li>The notice period has been checked against the grounds relied on, using the longest period that applies where multiple grounds are included.</li>
        <li>The earliest proceedings date shown in the pack is the date you intend to rely on if the claim is issued.</li>
        <li>The notice is signed and dated by the landlord or an authorised agent.</li>
        {{#if has_mandatory_ground}}
        <li>Where a mandatory ground is relied on, the evidence is still sufficient to prove the ground and any prerequisite facts at the hearing.</li>
        {{else}}
        <li>Where only discretionary grounds are relied on, the evidence explains why possession is reasonable in all the circumstances.</li>
        {{/if}}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout warning">
    <p><strong>Notice periods:</strong> The required notice period depends on the grounds relied on and can change. If you alter the grounds, the service method, or the intended service date, regenerate the pack so every document uses the same recalculated dates.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">After Service</h2>
  <div class="checklist-box">
    <div class="heading">Do Not Do These Things</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        {{#if (hasValue earliest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
        <li>Do not issue possession proceedings before {{earliest_proceedings_date_formatted}}.</li>
        {{/if}}
        <li>Do not change locks or remove belongings without a court order and lawful enforcement.</li>
        <li>Do not leave the service method or service evidence undocumented.</li>
        <li>Do not let one court-facing document use a different court name or notice timeline from the others.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout critical">
    <p><strong>Risk warning:</strong> A possession claim can be delayed or contested if the notice dates, service evidence, or grounds particulars are inconsistent across the pack, even where the underlying arrears or breach evidence is strong.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="doc-footer">
    <p><strong>Generated:</strong> {{generated_date}}</p>
    {{#unless clean_output}}
    <p><strong>Landlord Heaven</strong> | England Section 8 support document</p>
    {{/unless}}
  </div>
</body>
</html>
